<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If a bank blows up, there is a strict and well=
-known order of recovery, which is that depositors get all their money back=
 before shareholders of the bank get anything. This is a general rule of ba=
nkruptcy =E2=80=94=C2=A0creditors get paid before shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0but it=E2=80=99s particularly important in banking. Banks are very lever=
aged; they take lots of deposits with only a small sliver of equity. It is =
very important that those deposits be very=C2=A0<em>safe</em>, that they be=
, in the jargon, =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/29487703.291504/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmJlci5vcmcvcGFwZXJzL3cyNjA3NA/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2988b43c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> information insensitive</a>.=E2=80=
=9D The idea is that depositors should not have to do careful analysis of t=
heir bank=E2=80=99s health before depositing money. That=E2=80=99s the <em>=
shareholders=E2=80=99=C2=A0</em>job. The shareholders are on the hook for m=
ost of the losses, so, the theory goes, they will keep an eye on the banks=
=E2=80=99 managers and make sure they=E2=80=99re not doing anything too dum=
b.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are flaws in this theory, sure, but the =
alternative is probably worse. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29487703.291504/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjItMTAtMjQvY2Vsc2l1cy1zdG9ja2hvbGRlcnMtbG9zZS1iaWQtZm9yLW9mZmlja=
WFsLWJhbmtydXB0Y3ktY29tbWl0dGVlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMjUyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9t=
ZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTAyNSZ1dG1fY2F=
tcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB09ea8407" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Meanwh=
ile in crypto</a>!</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some Celsius stockholders are argu=
ing that they, rather than the company=E2=80=99s customers, are entitled to=
 the value from the crypto lender=E2=80=99s mining business and loan book b=
ecause of Celsius=E2=80=99s corporate structure. Lawyers for Celsius credit=
ors -- which are overwhelmingly its customers -- disagree.=C2=A0</p></block=
quote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To be fair, that=E2=80=99s from an article abo=
ut how the stockholders=C2=A0<em>lost </em>an effort to get appointed as an=
 official committee in the bankruptcy of Celsius Network, suggesting that t=
he judge is not all that sympathetic to their claims. Here=E2=80=99s how <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29487703.291504/aHR0=
cHM6Ly9jYXNlcy5zdHJldHRvLmNvbS9wdWJsaWMveDE5MS8xMTc0OS9QTEVBRElOR1MvMTE3NDk=
xMDI0MjI4MDAwMDAwMDAxOC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcdab3413" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> he=
 describes them</a>=C2=A0(citations omitted):</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Requesting Equity Holders=E2=
=80=99 legal position is that Celsius account holders do not hold claims at=
 each Debtor entity. Further, they argue that the Celsius Entities are, ess=
entially, a conglomerate of three business lines conducted by separate and =
distinct legal entities, including, without limitation: (i) the storage bus=
iness, which is conducted by GK8, whose equity the Debtors are seeking to s=
ell; (ii) the mining operations, which are conducted by Debtor Celsius Mini=
ng LLC (a subsidiary of CNL) and its non-Debtor subsidiary, Celsius Mining =
IL Ltd. (collectively, the =E2=80=9CMining Entities=E2=80=9D and, together =
with CNL and GK8, the =E2=80=9CNon-Customer Facing Entities=E2=80=9D); and =
(iii) the retail customer-facing business, which is conducted primarily thr=
ough Celsius Network LLC and is thus separate from the Non-Customer Facing =
Entities. The Requesting Equity Holders contend that only the equity holder=
s, and not Celsius account holders, have claims against Non-Customer Facing=
 Entities. The Debtors and Committee disagree and the Debtors have noted pu=
blicly that they believe Celsius account holders have claims against all De=
btor entities.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Celsius, they argue,=C2=A0is not so much a ban=
k whose depositors had senior claims on all of its money, and more of a vag=
ue agglomeration of businesses, most of which are entirely protected from d=
epositor claims. I do not have enough information to judge if that is corre=
ct. But it would be incredibly bad if it were!</p>
